[00:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hey there, my name is Hassan Raza and I\'m the co-founder and CEO here at Tavis. Today we\'re introducing Fenix 4, the most advanced real-time human rendering model today. At TAVIS, our research focuses on training machines to be amazing conversation partners with'

[00:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'humans with the timing, awareness, and emotional intelligence of real people. That requires more than just teaching machines to look the part, though. It involves modeling human behavior itself and teaching machines the nuances of'

[00:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'human connection and conversation. Fenix 4 is a unique hybrid gajon diffusion model trained on thousands of hours of human conversational data. The model generates each pixel at runtime allowing to have smooth and contextually accurate'

[00:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lip sync facial movements and head poses the fine degree of control. One of the most exciting capabilities of Fenix 4 is emotional intelligence. Fenix 4 isn\'t just generating facial movements based on audio waves. It has contextual'

[00:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'understanding of conversational dynamics and user emotions and uses those signals to produce emotionally rich responses. So instead of staying neutral or happy like previous models, Fenix 4 can'

[01:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'actually show things like anger, sadness, and a range of other emotions all in real time. And this isn\'t just mirroring the user either. Paired with our emotional perception system, Fenix 4 will react'

[01:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with the contextually correct emotion and change it on the fly naturally. &gt;&gt; Like you saw a ghost. &gt;&gt; What happened, &gt;&gt; dude? I was walking to work just now and a bird came out of nowhere and pooped'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'into my eye. &gt;&gt; That\'s freaking disgusting. You need to go wash that out ASAP. &gt;&gt; This unlocks a host of new use cases that require empathy and emotional intelligence, like in healthcare and therapy, while making all conversations'

[01:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with Tavis more humanlike. Honestly, I don\'t know if I can talk about my family right now. It\'s just very It\'s very difficult for me. &gt;&gt; That\'s completely okay. You don\'t have'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to talk about anything you\'re not ready for. &gt;&gt; Within that dance of interaction, one of the most critical and often overlooked elements is listening. Showing the unconscious signals that we understand and that we\'re present is vital for'

[02:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'natural conversation. And Fenix 4 is the only model that actually listens. It\'s a full duplex model, meaning that I can hear, understand, and react to what the user is saying in real time. It can nod'

[02:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to affirm you, stay still when nothing is going on, and even react emotionally to something you say. &gt;&gt; So, I just lost my job, and I I don\'t even know what happened. I He just called me into his office and fired me'

[02:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'immediately with no warning. &gt;&gt; Meanwhile, other realtime avatar models in the market today are one way. They only render out responses. So, in listening mode, they just cycle through pre-recorded listening animations, often'

[02:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'nodding when no one is speaking, blinking unnaturally, or just staying frozen, creating an uncanny and robotic experience. When Fenix 4 is done listening, it seamlessly transitions to talking, unlike models that snap or'

[02:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'unnaturally blend between rigid listening and talking states, or that fall back to traditional looping. Fenix 4 is capable of these seamless and natural transitions and incredible emotion in part because of its high'

[03:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'degree of controllability. The model controls facial behavior across multiple scales from head pose down to fine grain facial movements including individual eye gaze and blinks. Rather than'

[03:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'controlling these attributes explicitly or through scripted states though Fenix 4 employs a human behavioral model trained on a large amount of curated humanto human conversational data. This allows it to learn the nuances of human'

[03:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'conversation, reactions and expressions, things like your eyes crinkling when you smile or your brow furring when you frown and the context in which those occur. Learning the relationship between all parts of the face and head to'

[03:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'control them implicitly. The result is facial emotion that is natural, coherent, and has emergent micro expressions rather than being the result of explicitly programmed or loop states. And because of the unique architecture,'

[03:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'each replica\'s identity is preserved across long interactions, expressions, viewpoints, and emotional states. So realism never comes at the cost of consistency. All of this together allows for conversations that feel more'

[04:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'natural, present, and more immersive, and get us closer to being able to talk to machines like a friend or a co-orker. &gt;&gt; But it\'s actually good. It just means that we both have like excellent fashion sense, I think.'

[04:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; Oh, 100%. It\'s not just good, it\'s confirmation. &gt;&gt; This represents a much needed step towards emotionally intelligent human computing. Our goal with Fenix 4 was to give AI the ability to truly express'

[04:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'itself in real time. Together, Fenix 4 and our family of models, including Sparrow 1 for turn taking and Rave 1 for perception, allow tablet replicas and pals to communicate through more than just words, unlocking interactions that'

[04:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'feel fluid, expressive, and deeply human. You can go use Fenix 4 inside Tavis platform APIs and it Tavis pals starting today. See for yourself at tabs.io.'
